  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I saw this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, of course, we saw most of the Russian personnel basically getting out of town as fast as they could.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because there was a problem being that we were so close to the border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the German armies actually by then probably, sort of, bypassed our town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were probably ahead on the sides, so there was, like, a small window of opportunity to get out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you could get out still because we were not far from the city [POLISH], which was a railroad sort of junction, and if you got there, you were able to get on a train and still make it to Russia.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew-- we knew that war broke out, that the Germans attacked-- attacked Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, we did not know the significance of what was going to happen to Jews, although by then, we should have known because by 1941, the Germans already did a job on the Polish Jews that was under their occupation.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They already had a ghetto, I believe, in Lublin at that point, and they were already persecuting and killing Jews in a lesser way in the rest of Poland and Germany.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then-- it took a few days, and then suddenly, the Germans were marching into our town.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember being on that street.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were coming in on the main street that goes between [POLISH] and [POLISH] and [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I saw a little table, and the rabbi-- the rabbi and another man sitting at the table with bread and salt, which was a traditional way of welcoming, like, an invading army.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Germans were marching in the middle of the street, the main army.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
